{"type":"data","nodes":[null,{"type":"data","data":[{"tree":1},[2,26,45,59],{"slug":3,"title":4,"pages":5},"start","Start",[6,14,20],{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":8,"path":9,"title":10,"description":11,"order":12,"verified":13},"claw","install","/content/claw/docs/start/install.md","Install","Get the NullClaw binary via Homebrew, Docker, or a source build with Zig 0.16.0.",1,"v2026.5.29",{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":15,"path":16,"title":17,"description":18,"order":19,"verified":13},"quickstart","/content/claw/docs/start/quickstart.md","Quickstart","From a fresh install to a first conversation and a running gateway.",2,{"siteId":7,"section":3,"slug":21,"path":22,"title":23,"description":24,"order":25,"verified":13},"first-channel","/content/claw/docs/start/first-channel.md","Your first channel","Connect NullClaw to Telegram (or any of the 26 channels) and lock it down with allowlists.",3,{"slug":27,"title":28,"pages":29},"configure","Configure",[30,35,40],{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":31,"path":32,"title":33,"description":34,"order":12,"verified":13},"configuration","/content/claw/docs/configure/configuration.md","Configuration","One JSON file at ~/.nullclaw/config.json — OpenClaw-compatible, snake_case, no magic.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":36,"path":37,"title":38,"description":39,"order":19,"verified":13},"providers","/content/claw/docs/configure/providers.md","Providers","Connect ~60 model providers, set the default route, and add fallbacks and auto-routing.",{"siteId":7,"section":27,"slug":41,"path":42,"title":43,"description":44,"order":25,"verified":13},"memory","/content/claw/docs/configure/memory.md","Memory","Hybrid search over SQLite by default, nine other engines when you need them, and CLI tools to keep it clean.",{"slug":46,"title":47,"pages":48},"operate","Operate",[49,54],{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":50,"path":51,"title":52,"description":53,"order":12,"verified":13},"gateway-and-service","/content/claw/docs/operate/gateway-and-service.md","Gateway and service","Run NullClaw long-term — the HTTP gateway, pairing, cron endpoints, and background service mode.",{"siteId":7,"section":46,"slug":55,"path":56,"title":57,"description":58,"order":19,"verified":13},"security","/content/claw/docs/operate/security.md","Security","The layers NullClaw enforces by default, the settings that widen them, and how to audit for leaked secrets.",{"slug":60,"title":61,"pages":62},"reference","Reference",[63],{"siteId":7,"section":60,"slug":64,"path":65,"title":66,"description":67,"order":12,"verified":13},"cli","/content/claw/docs/reference/cli.md","CLI reference","Every nullclaw command, grouped by task — setup, runtime, channels, cron, memory, automation flags, and build flags."],"uses":{}},{"type":"data","data":[{"doc":1,"raw":10,"dateModified":31,"sectionTitle":32,"prev":33,"next":39},{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":4,"path":5,"title":6,"description":7,"order":8,"verified":9,"body":10,"html":11,"toc":12},"claw","configure","providers","/content/claw/docs/configure/providers.md","Providers","Connect ~60 model providers, set the default route, and add fallbacks and auto-routing.",2,"v2026.5.29","\nNullClaw talks to ~60 AI providers through one vtable interface — OpenRouter, Anthropic, OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, Gemini, Vertex AI, Ollama, Groq, Mistral, xAI, DeepSeek, Bedrock and more — plus any OpenAI-compatible endpoint you point it at.\n\n## Credentials\n\nProviders live under `models.providers`. Each entry takes at minimum an `api_key`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"models\": {\n    \"providers\": {\n      \"openrouter\": { \"api_key\": \"sk-or-...\" },\n      \"anthropic\": { \"api_key\": \"sk-ant-...\", \"base_url\": \"https://api.anthropic.com\" },\n      \"groq\": { \"api_key\": \"gsk_...\" }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nCommon per-provider fields:\n\n| Field | Purpose |\n| --- | --- |\n| `api_key` | Credential for that provider entry |\n| `base_url` | Override for custom or self-hosted OpenAI-compatible endpoints |\n| `api_mode` | `chat_completions` or `responses`, for compatible providers |\n| `user_agent` | Optional `User-Agent` header override |\n| `max_streaming_prompt_bytes` | Skip streaming above this estimated prompt size |\n\nWith `secrets.encrypt` enabled, API keys are encrypted at rest with ChaCha20-Poly1305 using a local key file.\n\n## The default model route\n\nThe default model is a `provider/vendor/model` route under `agents.defaults`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"model\": { \"primary\": \"openrouter/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\" }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nAny OpenAI-compatible API works via a custom route of the form `custom:https://your-api.com` — no code changes, no plugin.\n\n## Auto-routing with `model_routes`\n\nOptionally, NullClaw can pick a model per turn. Each route maps a hint to a provider and model; recognized hints are `fast`, `balanced`, `deep`, `reasoning`, and `vision`:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"model_routes\": [\n    { \"hint\": \"fast\", \"provider\": \"groq\", \"model\": \"llama-3.3-70b\", \"cost_class\": \"free\" },\n    { \"hint\": \"balanced\", \"provider\": \"openrouter\", \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\" },\n    { \"hint\": \"deep\", \"provider\": \"openrouter\", \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-opus-4\", \"cost_class\": \"premium\" }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nShort structured tasks prefer `fast`; investigation and planning prefer `deep`/`reasoning`; image turns use `vision`; everything ambiguous stays on `balanced`. Routes that hit rate limits are temporarily degraded and skipped until their cooldown expires.\n\nIn `nullclaw agent`:\n\n- `/model` shows the current model, routing status, and the last auto-route decision.\n- `/model \u003Cprovider/model>` pins the session and disables auto-routing.\n- `/model auto` clears the pin and re-enables routes.\n\nStarting with `--model` or `--provider` also pins the run.\n\n## Retries and fallbacks\n\nThe `reliability` section controls what happens when a provider fails:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"reliability\": {\n    \"provider_retries\": 2,\n    \"provider_backoff_ms\": 500,\n    \"fallback_providers\": [\"groq\", \"openai\"],\n    \"model_fallbacks\": [\n      { \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\", \"fallbacks\": [\"openai/gpt-4o\", \"groq/llama-3.3-70b\"] }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nIf you hold multiple keys for one provider, add `reliability.api_keys` and NullClaw rotates them on 429 errors.\n\n## Inspecting models from the CLI\n\n```bash\nnullclaw models list        # providers and default models\nnullclaw models info \u003Cmodel>\nnullclaw models benchmark   # model latency benchmark\nnullclaw models refresh     # refresh the model catalog\n```\n\nFor OAuth-based access, `nullclaw auth login openai-codex` runs a device flow (`--import-codex` imports existing `~/.codex/auth.json` credentials). `auth` currently supports only `openai-codex`.\n\n> [!TIP]\n> Vertex AI accepts either a bearer token or a full Google service-account JSON object as `api_key`. Service-account mode needs `openssl` on `$PATH` for JWT signing.\n\n## Next\n\nModels chosen — now decide what the agent remembers in [Memory](/docs/configure/memory/).\n","\u003Cp>NullClaw talks to ~60 AI providers through one vtable interface — OpenRouter, Anthropic, OpenAI, Azure OpenAI, Gemini, Vertex AI, Ollama, Groq, Mistral, xAI, DeepSeek, Bedrock and more — plus any OpenAI-compatible endpoint you point it at.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"credentials\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-credentials\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-credentials\">Credentials\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#credentials\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Credentials\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Providers live under \u003Ccode>models.providers\u003C/code>. Each entry takes at minimum an \u003Ccode>api_key\u003C/code>:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"json\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">{\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">models\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">providers\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">      \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">openrouter\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">api_key\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"sk-or-...\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">      \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">anthropic\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">api_key\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"sk-ant-...\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">base_url\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"https://api.anthropic.com\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">      \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">groq\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">api_key\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"gsk_...\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Common per-provider fields:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cdiv class=\"table-scroll\" role=\"region\" aria-label=\"Data table: Field, Purpose\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ctable>\n\u003Cthead>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Cth>Field\u003C/th>\n\u003Cth>Purpose\u003C/th>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/thead>\n\u003Ctbody>\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>api_key\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Credential for that provider entry\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>base_url\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Override for custom or self-hosted OpenAI-compatible endpoints\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>api_mode\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>chat_completions\u003C/code> or \u003Ccode>responses\u003C/code>, for compatible providers\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>user_agent\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Optional \u003Ccode>User-Agent\u003C/code> header override\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003Ctr>\n\u003Ctd>\u003Ccode>max_streaming_prompt_bytes\u003C/code>\u003C/td>\n\u003Ctd>Skip streaming above this estimated prompt size\u003C/td>\n\u003C/tr>\n\u003C/tbody>\n\u003C/table>\n\u003C/div>\n\u003Cp>With \u003Ccode>secrets.encrypt\u003C/code> enabled, API keys are encrypted at rest with ChaCha20-Poly1305 using a local key file.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"the-default-model-route\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-the-default-model-route\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-the-default-model-route\">The default model route\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#the-default-model-route\" aria-label=\"Permalink to The default model route\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>The default model is a \u003Ccode>provider/vendor/model\u003C/code> route under \u003Ccode>agents.defaults\u003C/code>:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"json\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">{\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">agents\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">defaults\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">      \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">primary\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"openrouter/anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Any OpenAI-compatible API works via a custom route of the form \u003Ccode>custom:https://your-api.com\u003C/code> — no code changes, no plugin.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"auto-routing-with-modelroutes\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-auto-routing-with-modelroutes\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-auto-routing-with-modelroutes\">Auto-routing with \u003Ccode>model_routes\u003C/code>\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#auto-routing-with-modelroutes\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Auto-routing with model_routes\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Optionally, NullClaw can pick a model per turn. Each route maps a hint to a provider and model; recognized hints are \u003Ccode>fast\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>balanced\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>deep\u003C/code>, \u003Ccode>reasoning\u003C/code>, and \u003Ccode>vision\u003C/code>:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"json\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">{\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model_routes\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> [\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">hint\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"fast\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">provider\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"groq\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"llama-3.3-70b\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">cost_class\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"free\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">hint\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"balanced\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">provider\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"openrouter\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> },\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">hint\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"deep\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">provider\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"openrouter\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"anthropic/claude-opus-4\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">cost_class\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"premium\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  ]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>Short structured tasks prefer \u003Ccode>fast\u003C/code>; investigation and planning prefer \u003Ccode>deep\u003C/code>/\u003Ccode>reasoning\u003C/code>; image turns use \u003Ccode>vision\u003C/code>; everything ambiguous stays on \u003Ccode>balanced\u003C/code>. Routes that hit rate limits are temporarily degraded and skipped until their cooldown expires.\u003C/p>\n\u003Cp>In \u003Ccode>nullclaw agent\u003C/code>:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cul>\n\u003Cli>\u003Ccode>/model\u003C/code> shows the current model, routing status, and the last auto-route decision.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Ccode>/model &lt;provider/model&gt;\u003C/code> pins the session and disables auto-routing.\u003C/li>\n\u003Cli>\u003Ccode>/model auto\u003C/code> clears the pin and re-enables routes.\u003C/li>\n\u003C/ul>\n\u003Cp>Starting with \u003Ccode>--model\u003C/code> or \u003Ccode>--provider\u003C/code> also pins the run.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"retries-and-fallbacks\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-retries-and-fallbacks\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-retries-and-fallbacks\">Retries and fallbacks\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#retries-and-fallbacks\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Retries and fallbacks\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>The \u003Ccode>reliability\u003C/code> section controls what happens when a provider fails:\u003C/p>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"json\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">{\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">reliability\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> {\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">provider_retries\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> 2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">provider_backoff_ms\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9A441\"> 500\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">fallback_providers\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> [\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">\"groq\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"openai\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">],\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model_fallbacks\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> [\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">      {\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">model\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> \"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">fallbacks\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">:\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> [\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">\"openai/gpt-4o\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">,\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> \"groq/llama-3.3-70b\"\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">]\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\"> }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">    ]\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">  }\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#8D8375\">}\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>If you hold multiple keys for one provider, add \u003Ccode>reliability.api_keys\u003C/code> and NullClaw rotates them on 429 errors.\u003C/p>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"inspecting-models-from-the-cli\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-inspecting-models-from-the-cli\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-inspecting-models-from-the-cli\">Inspecting models from the CLI\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#inspecting-models-from-the-cli\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Inspecting models from the CLI\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cfigure class=\"code-figure\" data-lang=\"bash\">\u003Cpre class=\"shiki null-kitchen\" style=\"background-color:#0a0806;color:#d9d1c3\" tabindex=\"0\">\u003Ccode>\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> models\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> list\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">        # providers and default models\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> models\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> info\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FF4F30\"> &#x3C;\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\">mode\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#D9D1C3\">l\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#FF4F30\">>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> models\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> benchmark\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">   # model latency benchmark\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\n\u003Cspan class=\"line\">\u003Cspan style=\"color:#ECE5D8\">nullclaw\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> models\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#C9B795\"> refresh\u003C/span>\u003Cspan style=\"color:#877E6F;font-style:italic\">     # refresh the model catalog\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/code>\u003C/pre>\u003Cbutton class=\"code-copy\" type=\"button\" data-code data-pagefind-ignore aria-live=\"polite\">copy\u003C/button>\u003C/figure>\n\u003Cp>For OAuth-based access, \u003Ccode>nullclaw auth login openai-codex\u003C/code> runs a device flow (\u003Ccode>--import-codex\u003C/code> imports existing \u003Ccode>~/.codex/auth.json\u003C/code> credentials). \u003Ccode>auth\u003C/code> currently supports only \u003Ccode>openai-codex\u003C/code>.\u003C/p>\n\u003Caside class=\"callout callout--tip\">\u003Cdiv class=\"callout-title\">Tip\u003C/div>\u003Cp>Vertex AI accepts either a bearer token or a full Google service-account JSON object as \u003Ccode>api_key\u003C/code>. Service-account mode needs \u003Ccode>openssl\u003C/code> on \u003Ccode>$PATH\u003C/code> for JWT signing.\u003C/p>\n\u003C/aside>\n\u003Ch2 id=\"next\" aria-labelledby=\"heading-label-next\">\u003Cspan id=\"heading-label-next\">Next\u003C/span>\u003Ca class=\"heading-anchor\" href=\"#next\" aria-label=\"Permalink to Next\" data-pagefind-ignore>\u003Cspan aria-hidden=\"true\">#\u003C/span>\u003C/a>\u003C/h2>\n\u003Cp>Models chosen — now decide what the agent remembers in \u003Ca href=\"/docs/configure/memory/\">Memory\u003C/a>.\u003C/p>\n",[13,16,19,22,25,28],{"id":14,"text":15,"depth":8},"credentials","Credentials",{"id":17,"text":18,"depth":8},"the-default-model-route","The default model route",{"id":20,"text":21,"depth":8},"auto-routing-with-modelroutes","Auto-routing with model_routes",{"id":23,"text":24,"depth":8},"retries-and-fallbacks","Retries and fallbacks",{"id":26,"text":27,"depth":8},"inspecting-models-from-the-cli","Inspecting models from the CLI",{"id":29,"text":30,"depth":8},"next","Next","2026-07-17","Configure",{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":34,"path":35,"title":36,"description":37,"order":38,"verified":9,"sectionTitle":32},"configuration","/content/claw/docs/configure/configuration.md","Configuration","One JSON file at ~/.nullclaw/config.json — OpenClaw-compatible, snake_case, no magic.",1,{"siteId":2,"section":3,"slug":40,"path":41,"title":42,"description":43,"order":44,"verified":9,"sectionTitle":32},"memory","/content/claw/docs/configure/memory.md","Memory","Hybrid search over SQLite by default, nine other engines when you need them, and CLI tools to keep it clean.",3],"uses":{"params":["section","slug"]}}]}
